.TH "usb4_port_retimer_write" 9 "usb4_port_retimer_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb4_port_retimer_write \- Write to retimer sideband registers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb4_port_retimer_write
.BI "(struct tb_port *port "  ","
.BI "u8 index "  ","
.BI "u8 reg "  ","
.BI "const void *buf "  ","
.BI "u8 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
USB4 port
.IP "index" 12
Retimer index
.IP "reg" 12
Sideband register to write
.IP "buf" 12
Data that is written starting from \fIreg\fP
.IP "size" 12
Number of bytes to write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Writes retimer sideband registers starting from \fIreg\fP. The retimer is
connected to \fIport\fP at \fIindex\fP. Returns 0 in case of success. If there
is no retimer present at given \fIindex\fP returns -ENODEV. In any other
failure returns negative errno.
